  "response": "No, Gotham does not share the same universe with Arrow and The Flash (which are part of the \"Arrowverse\").\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **Different Networks and Production:** Gotham aired on FOX, while Arrow and The Flash aired on The CW. While this isn't a *definitive* barrier, it's a significant factor against crossover potential. Different studios (Warner Bros. Television produced both Gotham and Arrowverse) would have to agree on terms for crossovers.\n*   **Distinct Tones and Styles:** Gotham has a unique, almost surreal, and hyper-stylized tone that doesn't mesh well with the more grounded, superhero-focused tone of the Arrowverse.\n*   **Inconsistencies in Characterization and Storytelling:** Gotham deviates significantly from established Batman lore in some areas, making it hard to reconcile with characters and storylines that would intersect with Arrow and The Flash.\n*   **No Crossovers:** Most conclusively, there have been no actual crossovers between Gotham and any Arrowverse show. Arrowverse shows are known for their frequent crossovers.\n\nWhile both share DC Comics origins, they exist in separate fictional universes.",
